<h3>I'm in! What do I do Now?</h3>
<p>To have a smooth advancement through the RN to BSN program once you are accepted, we suggest you do the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>Mail the Department of Nursing your properly completed Acceptance Form. Once received, your major code will be change to Bachelor of Science in Nursing.</li>
<li>Accept your placement with Brigham Young Univeristy - Idaho.</li>
<li>Create your BYU-Idaho login and password (if you haven't already) at <a href="http://www.byui.edu/netid" target="_self">www.byui.edu/netid</a>.</li>
<li>Review the following Baccalaureate of Science in Nursing web pages:  <ol>
<li><a href="x37088.xml">Clinical</a></li>
<li><a href="x37098.xml">Courses</a></li>
<li><a href="x37099.xml" style="outline-style: none; outline-width: initial; outline-color: initial; cursor: pointer;">Sample Completion</a></li>
<li><a href="x37104.xml" style="outline-style: none; outline-width: initial; outline-color: initial; cursor: pointer;">Forms and Applications</a></li>
<li><a href="x37111.xml">Course Sequence Petition</a></li>
</ol> </li>
<li>Get a 10-panel drug test. It is crucial this is done <strong>before</strong> you complete any clinical hours. This screening can be done at a facility of your choosing, or you can go to CertifiedBackground.com, click on "Student" and enter the code RG85DT to see other facilities that are available across the U.S.</li>
<li>Contact the College of Agriculture and Life Sciences Academic Discovery Center (<a href="mailto:CALSAcademicDiscoveryCenter@byui.edu" target="_self">CALSAcademicDiscoveryCenter@byui.edu</a> or 208-496-9830) to resolve any concerns regarding your Degree Audit.</li>
<li>Register for your RN to BSN course(s) and purchase needed textbooks.</li>
<li>Online students register for CTED online sections, on-campus students register for either DAY or CTED sections.</li>
</ol></div>
